oakcurric:unit-3465
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What are the strengths and weaknesses of the UK democratic system?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-are-the-strengths-and-weaknesses-of-the-uk-democratic-system" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils develop their knowledge of democracy and the different types of democracy
  considering the strengths and weaknesses of the UK system."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils learn about the strengths and weaknesses of the UK democratic
  system and build on their previous knowledge of basic political concepts and structures. This
  unit deepens their understanding of democracy, encouraging critical thinking about different
  types of governance and how democracy can be strengthened.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3465-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3465-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3465-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3465-4 ;
  curric:id "3465"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.518522Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-politics-parliament-and-government .

oakcurric:unit-3476
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Practising what we have learnt"@en ;
  curric:slug "practising-what-we-have-learnt" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils revisit a number of the key concepts covered in earlier units in
  preparation for their GCSE papers."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit brings together learning from across the entire sequence. It
  prepares students for answering questions in their GCSE by revisiting the key learning from
  each thread.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3476-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3476-2 ;
  curric:id "3476"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.686411Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3693
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How can we prepare well for financial decision making?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-can-we-prepare-well-for-financial-decision-making" ;
  rdfs:comment """Using the example of housing, pupils explore a range of different financial
  decisions, products and services. They consider how they can prepare to become financially
  independent and what advice is available to them."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils existing knowledge of personal and public
  spending and their understanding of debt, credit loans, savings investment and risk. Using
  the example of housing, students critically consider how personal and public spending and
  economic decisions can impact housing nationally.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3693-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3693-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3693-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3693-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3693-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3693-6 ;
  curric:id "3693"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.077126Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-finance-and-the-economy .

oakcurric:unit-3457
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Should the UK be called a democracy?"@en ;
  curric:slug "should-the-uk-be-called-a-democracy" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider what makes a democracy, they explore key features of democracy in
  the UK and consider how those in power are held to account."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils prior learning about what a democracy is.
  Pupils take a more in-depth look at how democracy works in the UK by exploring what
  parliament is, how we can hold those in power to account and the role of the press and media
  and select committees within democracy. The unit encourages critical thinking about
  governance, representation and citizens rights.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3457-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3457-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3457-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3457-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3457-5 ;
  curric:id "3457"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.168809Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-politics-parliament-and-government .

oakcurric:unit-3442
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Synopticity: How do different ideas and concepts in Citizenship interconnect?"@en ;
  curric:slug "synopticity-how-do-different-ideas-and-concepts-in-citizenship-interconnect" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils revisit key citizenship concepts from previous units and consider how they
  relate to each other, demonstrating their ability to draw together different areas of
  knowledge, skills and understanding."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit brings together learning from across the entire sequence. It
  prepares students for answering extended response questions in their GCSE which will relate
  to two of more specification themes.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3442-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3442-2 ;
  curric:id "3442"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.180445Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3473
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Why do we need the right to protest in a democracy?"@en ;
  curric:slug "why-do-we-need-the-right-to-protest-in-a-democracy" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils explore how rights have developed in the UK and how they are protected.
  They look at what changes in society have occurred due to protest."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding the necessity of the right to protest in a democracy builds
  on pupils' knowledge of rights, justice and the law and their knowledge of active
  citizenship. This unit explores the role of protest in influencing change and protecting
  freedoms. It challenges pupils to critically consider what methods are acceptable to create
  change, supporting them to develop as informed and responsible citizens.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3473-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3473-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3473-3 ;
  curric:id "3473"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.219591Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law .

oakcurric:unit-3456
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What tools can we use to challenge injustice in our communities?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-tools-can-we-use-to-challenge-injustice-in-our-communities" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider a diverse range of case studies to develop their understanding of
  how and why people challenge injustice in their communities."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils growing awareness of social issues and their
  potential roles as active citizens in addressing them. Understanding the tools to challenge
  injustice in our communities builds on their existing knowledge of civic responsibility and
  rights. This unit equips pupils with practical strategies and skills for active citizenship.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3456-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3456-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3456-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3456-4 ;
  curric:id "3456"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.416710Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law .

oakcurric:unit-3448
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How does identity affect rights?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-does-identity-affect-rights" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces pupils to the concept of multiply identities, pupils consider
  what impact different identities can have on rights."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding how identity affects rights builds on pupils' awareness of
  diversity and equality. This unit is timely as it asks pupils to critically think about the
  intersection of various identities with legal rights. By learning these concepts now, pupils
  can better advocate for themselves and others.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3448-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3448-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3448-3 ;
  curric:id "3448"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.512711Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-identities-and-communities .

oakcurric:unit-3464
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How can we make a difference in society? Active citizenship project"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-can-we-make-a-difference-in-society-active-citizenship-project" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils are introduced to what an active citizenship project is, how it should be
  structured and the skills they need to complete one."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on their learning of how they can make a positive difference in
  their communities this unit continues to develop pupils’ knowledge of social issues and the
  role citizens and organisations have in creating positive change. This knowledge helps pupils
  to understand how citizens can work together to improve communities and wider society and how
  they can make their voice heard by those in positions of power.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3464-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3464-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3464-3 ;
  curric:id "3464"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.537724Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-active-citizenship-making-a-positive-difference .

oakcurric:unit-3471
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How is UK society diverse and changing?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-is-uk-society-diverse-and-changing" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils explore what identity is and how the UK population is changing considering
  how diverse the UK is and exploring mutual respect and understanding between different
  groups within society."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on prior learning around identities and communities this unit
  analyses what identity is, how it can evolve over time and the impact this has on the
  population and communities in the UK. Through exploring these concepts now pupils can better
  understand and engage with a range of diverse communities, preparing them to be informed and
  active citizens.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3471-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3471-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3471-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3471-4 ;
  curric:id "3471"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.622900Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-identities-and-communities .

oakcurric:unit-3466
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What are the strengths and weaknesses of the legal system?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-are-the-strengths-and-weaknesses-of-the-legal-system" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils learn how laws are made and enforced and about the purpose and types of
  punishment."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils foundational understanding of law and its role
  in society. Pupils examine the strengths and weaknesses of the legal system critically
  evaluating how laws are applied and enforced in the UK. This knowledge helps them recognise
  the distinct roles and responsibilities within the legal system, fostering informed and
  active citizenship as they deepen their level of engagment with politcal and social ideas
  affecting society.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3466-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3466-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3466-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3466-4 ;
  curric:id "3466"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.657856Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law .

oakcurric:unit-3475
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Where does power reside in the UK?"@en ;
  curric:slug "where-does-power-reside-in-the-uk" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils look at the role of local and national government and identify reserved and
  devolved powers in the UK."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils explore the distribution of power within their country.
  Understanding where power resides in the UK builds on their knowledge of power and
  government. By exploring these concepts now, pupils can critically evaluate how power is
  allocated and exercised and how they can bring their voice to power, preparing them for
  informed participation in civic life.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3475-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3475-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3475-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3475-4 ;
  curric:id "3475"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.665883Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-politics-parliament-and-government .

oakcurric:unit-3443
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How do democratic systems work around the world?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-do-democratic-systems-work-around-the-world" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils explore how key democratic structures such as the justice system, the media
  and government operate across the globe and consider the impact this has on human rights
  and citizens ability to take action."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Learning how democratic systems work around the world builds on their
  knowledge of government and democracy within the UK. This unit provides a comparative
  perspective on different democratic practices and institutions. By exploring these concepts
  now, pupils can appreciate the diversity of democratic systems and critically consider the
  pros and cons of different democractic systems.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3443-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3443-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3443-3 ;
  curric:id "3443"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.951270Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-uk-and-the-wider-world .

oakcurric:unit-3470
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How does the UK play a role in the international community?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-does-the-uk-play-a-role-in-the-international-community" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider the role the UK plays in Europe and the wider world, exploring
  organisations such as the United Nations and WTO and examining what role the UK has in
  global problems."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding how the UK plays a role in the international community
  builds on pupils' knowledge of politics and global issues. This unit is timely as it explores
  the UK's contributions to international organizations, diplomacy, and global challenges. By
  learning these concepts now, pupils can better understand the UK's global impact and their
  role as global citizens.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3470-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3470-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3470-3 ;
  curric:id "3470"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.382876Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3472
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What is the nature of the British Constitution?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-is-the-nature-of-the-british-constitution" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils consider why we need a separation of powers and whether the
  current political structures are fit for purpose."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on earlier units on democracy and the UK political system, this
  unit further explores the nature of the British constitution. The unit provides critical
  insights into how the UK political system operates encouraging students to think critically
  about the pros and cons of the current system. Understanding the nature of the British
  constitution is essential learning for informed civic participation.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3472-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3472-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3472-3 ;
  curric:id "3472"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.573331Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-politics-parliament-and-government .

oakcurric:unit-3474
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How do others govern?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-do-others-govern" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils compare different types of government from the UK to US and North
  Korea."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding how others govern builds on pupils' existing knowledge of
  the UK political system. This unit broadens pupils comparative understanding of different
  governmental structures and practices worldwide. By exploring these concepts now, pupils can
  critically assess the effectiveness of various governance models and examine the diversity of
  political systems and the impact this has.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3474-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3474-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3474-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3474-4 ;
  curric:id "3474"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.700977Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-politics-parliament-and-government .

oakcurric:unit-3910
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Why is the rule of law important?"@en ;
  curric:slug "why-is-the-rule-of-law-important" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit analyses how the rule of law operates in contemporary Britain. Pupils
  evaluate threats to fairness, including inequality, abuse of power and barriers to
  justice, and examine the role of citizens in upholding the law."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ understanding of legal systems by focusing on
  evaluation and application in real-world contexts.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3910-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3910-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3910-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3910-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3910-5 ;
  curric:id "3910"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.724753Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 .

oakcurric:unit-3455
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How are community identities changing?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-are-community-identities-changing" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils explore the concepts of identity, community, migration and
  belonging."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on their learning from key stage 3 pupils explore what makes a
  community and how the nature of communities can change over time. Understanding the
  complexity of identities and communities is crucial for their awareness of diversity and
  their sense of belonging. This learning helps pupils to reflect on their own identities,
  understanding others and contribute positively in their communities.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3455-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3455-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3455-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3455-4 ;
  curric:id "3455"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.895533Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-identities-and-communities .

oakcurric:unit-3454
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How does the international community respond to global humanitarian problems?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-does-the-international-community-respond-to-global-humanitarian-problems" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider what role the UK should have in tackling international conflict
  and global humanitarian problems, exploring different methods for conflict resolution."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding the international community's response to global
  humanitarian problems builds on pupils' knowledge of UK and the wider world. This unit is
  timely as it examines mechanisms and strategies for addressing crises. By learning these
  concepts now, pupils can appreciate the role of international cooperation in solving global
  challenges, fostering a sense of global citizenship.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3454-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3454-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3454-3 ;
  curric:id "3454"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.938002Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-uk-and-the-wider-world .

oakcurric:unit-3444
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How can we play a part in the legal system?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-can-we-play-a-part-in-the-legal-system" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider a range of roles within the legal system, explore what rights
  citizens have within the justice system and what influence they can have on the law."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Learning how they can play a part in the legal system builds on pupils'
  knowledge of law and governance. This unit is timely as it highlights opportunities for
  active participation, such as jury duty, volunteering, or legal advocacy. This knowledge
  helps pupils understand the role of citizens in the justice system, preparing them for active
  and engaged citizenship.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3444-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3444-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3444-3 ;
  curric:id "3444"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.012794Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law .

oakcurric:unit-3458
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How can I be a changemaker in my community?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-can-i-be-a-changemaker-in-my-local-community" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit enables students to build knowledge and understanding of communities and
  develop active citizenship skills to make a positive change."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Learning how to be a changemaker in their local community builds on
  pupils' knowledge of active citizenship. This unit provides practical tools and strategies
  for community engagement and advocacy. By exploring these concepts now, pupils are empowered
  to take initiative and drive positive change in their communities, preparing them to be
  active and engaged citizens.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3458-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3458-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3458-3 ;
  curric:id "3458"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.074022Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-active-citizenship-making-a-positive-difference .

oakcurric:unit-3446
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How well has the UK adjusted to its changing relationship with the EU?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-well-has-the-uk-adjusted-to-its-changing-relationship-with-the-eu" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils analyse the reasons behind the Brexit referendum and consider what the
  implications of it have been."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding how the UK has adjusted to its changing relationship with
  the EU builds on pupils' knowledge of the UK and the wider world. This unit is timely as it
  explores the political, economic, and social adjustments post-Brexit. By learning these
  concepts now, pupils can critically evaluate the impacts and ongoing challenges""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3446-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3446-2 ;
  curric:id "3446"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.076065Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-uk-and-the-wider-world .

oakcurric:unit-3453
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How can politicians involve citizens in direct decision making?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-can-politicians-involve-citizens-in-direct-decision-making" ;
  rdfs:comment """Through a series of case studies from across the globe pupils explore different
  methods of direct democracy and consider how UK citizens can play a part in shaping
  national policy."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding how politicians can involve citizens in direct
  decision-making builds on pupils knowledge of politics, parliament and government and their
  active citizenship skills. This unit is timely as it highlights mechanisms like referendums
  and consultations, exploring different methods for citizens to make their voices heard. By
  learning these concepts now, pupils can advocate for and participate in direct democratic
  processes now and in the future.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3453-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3453-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3453-3 ;
  curric:id "3453"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.294731Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-politics-parliament-and-government .

oakcurric:unit-3452
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How effective is the UN and SDGs on promoting sustainability?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-effective-is-the-un-and-sdgs-on-promoting-sustainability" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider what role international organisations play in sustainability and
  climate justice."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding the effectiveness of the UN on climate change builds on
  pupils' knowledge of the UK and the wider world. This unit assesses international efforts to
  combat climate change. By learning these concepts now, pupils can critically evaluate the
  UN's role and efficacy. This supports pupils to develop informed and researched opinions
  toward sustainability.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3452-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3452-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3452-3 ;
  curric:id "3452"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.636834Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-uk-and-the-wider-world .

oakcurric:unit-3451
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How is social media changing our view of democracy?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-is-social-media-changing-our-view-of-democracy" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider the impact that new forms of media are having on democracy using
  case studies from the UK and India."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding how social media is changing our view of democracy builds on
  pupils' knowledge of governance and media influence. This unit is timely as it explores the
  impact of social media on political engagement, information dissemination, and public
  opinion. By learning these concepts now, pupils can critically assess digital media's role in
  democracy, making this education crucial for developing informed and discerning citizens.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3451-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3451-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3451-3 ;
  curric:id "3451"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.667319Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-role-of-media-and-digital-democracy .

oakcurric:unit-3445
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What can we do to reduce crime?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-can-we-do-to-reduce-crime" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils explore how crime impacts the UK and consider the purpose of sentencing and
  whether current sentencing approaches in the UK are effective."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding what can be done to reduce crime builds on their knowledge
  of rights, justice and the law. This unit explores strategies for crime prevention and
  rehabilitation. By learning these concepts now, pupils can contribute to creating safer
  communities through informed actions and advocacy.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3445-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3445-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3445-3 ;
  curric:id "3445"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.695003Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law .

oakcurric:unit-3463
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How does the media hold those in power to account?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-does-the-media-hold-those-in-power-to-account" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils consider what role the media plays in democracy and how the media is used
  to hold those in power to account. They consider what responsible journalism is and the
  impact of misinformation."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on their key stage three learning about how the media impacts
  them this unit explores the important role the media plays within democracy. Through
  exploring concepts such as responsible journalism, censorship and misinformation pupils
  critically consider the importance of a free press to society.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3463-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3463-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3463-3 ;
  curric:id "3463"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.727248Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-role-of-media-and-digital-democracy .

oakcurric:unit-3692
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How do we look after an ageing population?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-do-we-look-after-an-ageing-population" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils explore what role financial systems play in our communities, they consider
  what personal responsibility they have for financial planning and what role government
  plays in this, focussing on the impact our ageing population has on financial planning."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit pupils take their existing knowledge on personal and public
  finances and consider how our financial systems are responding to the changing population and
  the impact this is having. The unit builds on knowledge of both personal and government
  spending and encourages students to think critically about spending responsibilities across
  society.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3692-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3692-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3692-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3692-4 ;
  curric:id "3692"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.728946Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-finance-and-the-economy .

oakcurric:unit-3450
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How powerful is the media?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-powerful-is-the-media" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils explore the power and influence of the media both locally and nationally
  and consider how citizens can effectively navigate the information they are presented
  with."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding how powerful the media is builds on pupils knowledge of the
  media and its role within a democractic society. This unit is timely as it examines the
  media's role in shaping perceptions, influencing policy, and holding power to account. By
  learning these concepts now, pupils can critically evaluate media content and its impact on
  society, preparing them to be media literate and informed citizens.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3450-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3450-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3450-3 ;
  curric:id "3450"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.730796Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-role-of-media-and-digital-democracy .

oakcurric:unit-3467
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How does the economy work?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-does-the-economy-work" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils learn what the economy is, what taxes are and consider local and central
  government spending and risk management."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on prior learning around personal finance and managing
  money through looking at basic economic concepts and principles. Pupils examines how the UK
  Government manages its finances and the impact on citizens and public services. By the end,
  pupils will understand the balance between economic decisions, taxation, and public service
  provision in the UK.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3467-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3467-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3467-3 ;
  curric:id "3467"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.745421Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-finance-and-the-economy .

oakcurric:unit-3459
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What has the UK economy got to do with me?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-has-the-uk-economy-got-to-do-with-me" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops pupils' knowledge and understanding of the UK economy and helps
  them appreciate its relevance to them."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding what the UK economy has to do with them builds on pupils
  existing knowledge of personal finance and basic economic concepts. The unit helps pupils
  connect macroeconomic concepts to their personal experiences, such as income, credit, debt
  and taxation. By learning these concepts now, pupils can better understand how economic
  policies and trends affect their future decisions and prospects.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3459-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3459-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3459-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3459-4 ;
  curric:id "3459"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.754801Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-finance-and-the-economy .

oakcurric:unit-3460
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Does our legal system protect citizens' rights?"@en ;
  curric:slug "does-our-legal-system-protect-citizens-rights" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit builds pupils knowledge and understanding of the law and the legal
  system including: criminal and civil justice; the judicial process and role of citizens in
  justice; legal rights, sanctions; and how well prison works."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Understanding how the legal system protects citizens' rights builds on
  their knowledge of the key concepts of law and rights. This unit takes these concepts and
  looks at how they relate to each other. By learning to consider these concepts synoptically
  now, pupils can better understand their rights and the legal protections available to them.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3460-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3460-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3460-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3460-4 ;
  curric:id "3460"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.771997Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-rights-justice-and-the-law .

oakcurric:unit-3449
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "How can the local economy support sustainability?"@en ;
  curric:slug "how-can-the-local-economy-support-sustainability" ;
  rdfs:comment """Using the example of sustainability, students consider the local economy and its
  impact on citizens and their local communities."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Exploring how the local economy can support sustainability builds on
  pupils' knowledge of finance and the economy. This unit is timely as it highlights
  sustainable practices and their importance for future generations. By learning these concepts
  now, pupils can advocate for and engage in sustainable economic activities.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3449-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3449-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3449-3 ;
  curric:id "3449"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.777449Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-finance-and-the-economy .

oakcurric:unit-3461
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "What are the different ways we can become involved in politics?"@en ;
  curric:slug "what-are-the-different-ways-we-can-become-involved-in-politics" ;
  rdfs:comment """Pupils build knowledge and understanding of political systems, government, voting
  and elections. Pupils consider the vast range of political roles, exploring the impact
  that these roles can have across local communities and wider society and how they can get
  involved in politics."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on their growing knowledge of democracy, this unit further
  develops students understanding of political systems and civic engagement. The unit provides
  insight into how the UK political system and political systems around the world operate and
  examines the skills needed for a variety of roles within politics. This knowledge helps them
  to recognise the distinct roles and responsibilities within politics, fostering informed and
  active citizenship.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3461-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3461-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3461-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3461-4 ;
  curric:id "3461"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.884365Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-citizenship-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-politics-parliament-and-government .

